# React Patterns — web_app

## Components
- Functional components with `function` declarations and TypeScript interfaces
- Declarative JSX; minimize imperative effects
- Place static content and interfaces at file end; content constants outside render
- Named exports; avoid default exports

## Server/Client
- Minimize `use client`; prefer RSC where possible
- Wrap client components in `Suspense` with fallbacks
- Dynamic import for non-critical components

## Forms
- `react-hook-form` + Zod; `useActionState` for server actions error flow
- Model expected errors as return values; avoid try/catch for expected states

## Images
- Prefer WebP; specify width/height; lazy load non-critical images

## Example
```tsx
export function UserCard({ user }: { user: User }) {
  if (!user) return null
  return (
    <section>
      <h3>{user.name}</h3>
      <p>{user.email}</p>
    </section>
  )
}

// interfaces at end
interface User { id: string; name: string; email: string }
```